                    <p>Despite world progress toward simplicity in every sphere, the underlying processes that produce such simplicity might be complicated. Consequently, people without technical knowledge need a report to document these complex technical processes. Moreover, technical writing must be able to convey technical strategies and ideas to nontechnical readers.</p>
                    <p>Unlike fictional writing, content writing, business copywriting, and other forms of writing, technical writing requires a different style. The purpose of other types of writing may be entertainment, education, or selling products. For example, a technical report writer explains complicated information in a way that readers without technical knowledge can understand.</p>
                    <h2 class="section-title">What is <span>Technical Writing</span></h2>
                    <p>The term technical writing is used to describe the documentation of complex technical processes. Such documentation can form reports, executive summaries, and briefs. By definition, technical writing is the communication of technical information in writing.</p>
                    <p>Among these are high-tech manufacturing, aerospace, engineering, biotechnology, energy, finance, and information technology. </p>
                    <p>There is no longer a requirement for lengthy user guides. However, it is imperative that technical information be concise and presented clearly. This information can be found in technical reports, emails, policy briefs, and press releases.</p>
                    <h2 class="section-title"><span>The Primacy of  </span> Technical Writing</h2>
                    <p>Various applications of technical writing are evident in both consumer products and industrial settings. For example, without precise, clear writing explaining the specifications and directions for use, products can become meaningless at best and potentially dangerous. On the other hand, the technical documents ensure products are used as intended, even if constructing and using equipment and methods are possible without reading them.</p>
